        <div class="border border-hairline rounded-lg bg-canvas overflow-hidden shadow-lvl1">
          <button 
            type="button"
            class="faq-toggle w-full px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between text-left font-sans text-sm font-bold text-ink hover:bg-canvas-soft-2 transition-colors cursor-pointer"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            <span>How is my monthly mortgage payment calculated?</span>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-content hidden border-t border-hairline px-6 py-4 bg-canvas-soft">
            <p class="text-body text-sm font-sans leading-relaxed">
              Your monthly principal and interest payment is calculated using the standard amortization formula: <strong>M = P * [r(1+r)^n] / [(1+r)^n - 1]</strong>, where P is the loan principal (home price minus down payment), r is the monthly interest rate (annual rate divided by 12), and n is the total number of payments (loan term in years multiplied by 12). Property taxes, home insurance, homeowners association (HOA) fees, and private mortgage insurance (PMI) are then added to this baseline amount to determine your total monthly payment.
            </p>
          </div>
